First define primary colors, font style and font size on the :root section of the CSS file.

Classes and id  

<code>.nav</code> 

Define responsive menu

<code>#menu-toggle</code>

Use for burger on small screen, set a 600px max.

<code>.bar-1</code> to <code>bar-3</code> just use for styling the burger

<code>.content</code> Class

This class can be use for styling in separate way the content go throuth the main page on an Eleventy site.

<code>.grid-container</code>  Class

Is the main container for responsive content on columns.

<code>.column</code> Class
Define a container for hold a group of column distribution. 

<code>.col-1</code> to <code>col-10</code>

The Grid is divided on 10 equal individual columns. In this way a row can only hold a maximun of 10 columns or equivalent distribution.

Eg. A row with a col-5, col-3 and a col-2 is equal to a col-10 and occupy the same width.


		<div class="grid-container">
			<div class="column col-5>Esta ocupa cinco columnas</div>
			<div class="column col-3>Esta ocupa tres columnas</div>
			<div class="column col-2>Esta ocupa dos columnas</div>
		</div>

As you can see the simplest way is to use the col number as the width you want to occupy.

Heading Sizes
Not much secret here. Just ajust the points you want to use for each one at the root section. That's it!
You can you the variables to personalize the headings as you want to.
